abstract: The media has a bigger problem than liberal bias.
snippet: The media has a bigger problem than liberal bias.
lead_paragraph: John F. Harris is about as mainstream as the mainstream media gets. He spent 21 years at The Washington Post, including as its political editor. Then he became the founding editor of Politico, where he is now a columnist.

abstract: After four seasons, USA Network’s cybersecurity thriller comes to an end. And a Christmas movie from Disney+ is available to stream.
snippet: After four seasons, USA Network’s cybersecurity thriller comes to an end. And a Christmas movie from Disney+ is available to stream.
lead_paragraph: MR. ROBOT 9 p.m. on USA Network. This month, Rami Malek earned his third Golden Globe nomination for his lead role as the tortured vigilante hacker in this cyberthriller series. Elliot (Malek) and Mr. Robot (Christian Slater) have come a long way. In last week’s episode (spoiler alert!), Elliot and Whiterose (BD Wong) shared their vision for humanity in a tense philosophical debate before the creation of a seemingly parallel universe. And, if that weren’t enough of a cliffhanger, Elliot came face to face with his hooded doppelgänger and asked the burning question: “Who are you?” Catch the reveal in this two-part series finale.

headline_main: What’s on TV Sunday: ‘Mr. Robot’ and ‘Noelle’

abstract: The final Democratic debate of the year took place against the backdrop of a House vote to impeach President Trump. Here’s a recap.
snippet: The final Democratic debate of the year took place against the backdrop of a House vote to impeach President Trump. Here’s a recap.
lead_paragraph: It appears nobody consulted the Jedi Council before scheduling a Democratic debate on the same night that “Star Wars: The Rise of Skywalker” opened. So if you missed it, or any of the other happenings on the 2020 campaign trail this week, we’re here to help.

abstract: “It’s just not fair,” said the owner of the wine cave, who with his wife has donated millions to Democrats since the 1980s.
snippet: “It’s just not fair,” said the owner of the wine cave, who with his wife has donated millions to Democrats since the 1980s.
lead_paragraph: RUTHERFORD, Calif. — To reach the wine cave that set off a firestorm in this week’s Democratic presidential debate, visitors must navigate a hillside shrouded in mossy oak trees and walk down a brick-and-limestone hallway lined with wine barrels. Inside the room, a strikingly long table made of wood and onyx sits below a raindrop chandelier with 1,500 Swarovski crystals.

abstract: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
snippet: Elizabeth Warren, Pete Buttigieg and Amy Klobuchar are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — As Elizabeth Warren and Amy Klobuchar escalated their attacks on Pete Buttigieg in Thursday night’s Democratic debate, and Mr. Buttigieg forcefully pushed back, a crucial if unspoken fact was driving the political combat: All three candidates are trying to knock each other out in the Iowa caucuses, where they need strong finishes to stay viable in the 2020 race.

abstract: Christianity Today’s call for President Trump’s removal gave voice to his evangelical critics. But they remain a minority in a political movement that Mr. Trump has reshaped in his own mold.

lead_paragraph: The publication is small, reaching just a fraction of the evangelical movement.

abstract: Only Joe Biden, Pete Buttigieg, Amy Klobuchar, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren have met the new criteria to take part in the debate, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines.
snippet: Only Joe Biden, Pete Buttigieg, Amy Klobuchar, Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren have met the new criteria to take part in the debate, scheduled for Jan. 14 in Des Moines.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — One day after seven candidates took the stage for the most intimate debate of the Democratic presidential primary cycle so far, the Democratic National Committee increased the qualification standards for its next debate in January, making it likely that the field of candidates will be winnowed even further for the event.
